Laymans definition :- (non technical definition)

Cloud native applications are software applications which are designed in such way so they can take advantages of cloud native technologies.
These applications are build to run optimized to run in cloud enviroments.

The cloud native computing definition foundation definition :-

Cloud-native technologies empower organizations to build and run scalable applications in modern, dynamic environments such as public, private, and hybrid clouds. 
Containers, service meshes, microservices, immutable infrastructure, and declarative APIs exemplify this approach.

n simpler terms, cloud-native computing focuses on building applications that leverage the cloud's full potential. 
It emphasizes scalability, flexibility, and automation, using technologies like containers (Docker, Kubernetes), microservices, and CI/CD pipelines to ensure rapid development, deployment, and management of applications.


